{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require all new tall buildings to have pumped storage systems",
        "additional_details": "This should help overcome the problems of storing excess power from renewables, for the times when the wind is not blowing or it's night-time. All technology exists now.\r\n \r\nArchitects could incorporate this in their designs e.g. in an atrium with transparent tubing.\r\n \r\nThe water could also be used as a reservoir during droughts, and to supply sprinklers in case of fire.",
        "background": "The Government should require all new buildings of a certain height to have pumped storage systems, where excess power can be used to pump water to roof tanks, to be released (when renewables output falls) into basement water turbines . This is a smaller local version of \"Electric Mountain\" in Wales",
